React Learning Path - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q9Qx2Xef0do
==============================================================================

1. Fundamentals
    a) create react app
    b) function components
    c) class components
    d) jsx
    e) props & state
    f) useState & useEffect hooks
    g) setState & component lifecycle methods
    h) conditional rendering
    i) lists & key
    j) building simple forms

2. Advanced
    a) context
    b) higher order components
    c) render props
    d) refs
    e) error boundaries
    f) portals
    g) http requests
        1) get
        2) post
    h) hooks
        1) useContext
        2) useReducer
        3) useRef
        4) useMemo
        5) useCallback
        6) custom hooks

3. Ecosystem
    a) state management
        1) redux/mobx
        2) apollo client
    b) routing
        1) react router
    c) styling
        1) styled components / emotion
        2) tailwind css 
        3) chakra ui / material ui / ant design
    d) forms
        1) formik
        2) react hook forms
    f) testing
        1) jest + react testing library
        2) cypress
    g) miscellaneous
        1) typescript
        2) storybook
        3) react i18next
        4) Firebase
        5) practical react libraries
    h) next steps
        1) gatsby
        2) next.js
        3) react native
    
4. Tooling & Misc
    a) code editor (vscode)
    b) version control (git)
    c) linters (eslint)
    d) code formatters (prettier)
    e) browse dev tools
    f) bundlers ( webpack, snowpack, rollup, parcel)
    g) typescript